      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'm so sorry you're going through this; losing everything feels like a crushing weight, but your parents' disappointment is likely far more temporary than the financial loss you're facing. Often, people who suddenly lose their status or resources actually become more beloved in the long run because their true worth was never tied to those external things. Please consider speaking with a therapist or counselor who can help you navigate this grief and rebuild your sense of self outside of your former achievements.",
