      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That heavy burden of shame is incredibly painful, but you are not solely responsible for the future stability of your family; you did your best with the resources you had at the time. The \"stain\" you perceive is often a projection of your own guilt rather than a truth, and it is entirely possible for you to be forgiven and to rebuild a new chapter that honors your resilience. Many people who feel they have ruined everything find that their loved ones eventually understand their struggle, and that a fresh start is not just possible but necessary for your healing.",
